il  long after chemical acquired chase in  irving picard the sipc receiver appointed to liquidate madoffs company alleged that jpmorgan failed to prevent madoff from defrauding his customers according to the suit chase knew or should have known that madoffs wealth management business was a fraud however chase did not report its concerns to regulators or law enforcement until october  when it notified the uk serious organised crime agency picard argued that even after morgan investment bankers reported its concerns about madoffs performance to uk officials chases retail banking division did not put any restrictions on madoffs banking activities until his arrest two months later the receivers suit against jp morgan was dismissed by the court for failing to set forth any legally cognizable claim for damages in the fall of  jpmorgan began talks with prosecutors and regulators regarding compliance with antimoneylaundering and knowyourcustomer banking regulations in connection with madoff on january   jpmorgan agreed to pay a total of  billion in fines and penalties to settle civil and criminal charges related to its role in the madoff scandal the government filed a twocount criminal information charging jpmorgan with bank secrecy act violations but the charges will be dismissed within two years provided that jpmorgan reforms its antimoney laundering procedures and cooperates with the government in its investigation the bank agreed to forfeit  billion the lawsuit which was filed on behalf of shareholders against chief executive jamie dimon and other highranking jpmorgan employees used statements made by bernie madoff during interviews conducted while in prison in butner north carolina claiming that jpmorgan officials knew of the fraud the lawsuit stated that jpmorgan was uniquely positioned for  years to see madoffs crimes and put a stop to them  but faced with the prospect of shutting down madoffs account and losing lucrative profits jpmorgan  at its highest level  chose to turn a blind eye  jpmorgan also agreed to pay a  million fine to the office of the comptroller of the currency and settle the suit filed against it by picard for  million corruption investigation in asiaedit on march   the hong kong independent commission against corruption seized computer records and documents after searching the office of fang the companys outgoing chief executive officer for china investment banking september  cyberattackedit main article  jpmorgan chase data breach a cyberattack disclosed in september  compromised the jpmorgan chase accounts of over  million customers the attack was discovered by the banks security team in late july  but not completely halted until the middle of august alleged discrimination lawsuitedit in january  the united states sued the company accusing it of discriminating against thousands of black and hispanic mortgage borrowers between  and at least  staff suicideedit  january  around  am gabriel magee a male american senior it programmer aged  jump down  feet from the roof of the story  bank street the european headquarter in canary wharf london gabriel magee was found dead on the th floor roof which partially surrounds  bank street building officesedit although the old chase manhattan banks headquarters were located at one chase manhattan plaza now known as  liberty street in downtown manhattan the current world headquarters for jpmorgan chase  co are located at  park avenue chemical banks former headquarters the bulk of north american operations take place in four buildings located adjacent to each other on park avenue in new york city the former union carbide building at  park avenue the hub of sales and trading operations and the original chemical bank building at  park avenue where most investment banking activity took place asset and wealth management groups are located at  park avenue and  park avenue other groups are located in the former bear stearns building at  madison avenue chase the us and canada reta